                  <persName id="t18280410-229-person1288">
                  LYDIA 
                  GODSON
               <interp inst="t18280410-229-person1288" type="surname" value="GODSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-229-person1288" type="given" value="LYDIA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-229-person1288" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of John Godson, <rs id="t18280410-229-viclabel1224" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-229-victim1287 t18280410-229-viclabel1224"></join>, of Kingsland-road; the prisoner has lodged with us for three years, with her husband. On the 7th of March I met her in Thomas-street, Hackney-road, and said, "That is my chair you have got;" she said, "No, it is a friend's - I am going to take it home;" I then thought it was not mine, and went home; she did not come home all night, and next morning, we found their door open, and missed all these articles - they had never slept out before; nothing but two chairs were left; we have found nothing but two chairs; she told us where she had sold the other things, but the people had sold them again - she never returned; I went next morning, and at the corner of Kingsland-road saw her and her husband; I laid hold of him, and she ran away; I called Stop thief! and she was taken by my husband: she said she had taken the things, and pawned and sold them.</p>
               <p>
            
